content.rendered: Facial cosmetic surgery is a branch of surgery which covers the treatment of bone and soft tissues of the head and neck region. It usually involves surgery to cure infections, remove unwanted growth, correct bony mal-alignment, correct jaw functions, repair bony fractures and biopsy. Cosmetic Surgery is often done by an oral surgeon or oral maxillofacial surgeon with the help of Cosmetic Surgery assistant. Cosmetic Surgery cost varies depending on the severity and difficulty of the cases.
